<item>
            <title>[HBASE-4026] Explicit management of buffer lifecycle in the block cache</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4026</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The HBase block cache can be problematic because it is unpredictable when Java will reclaim the unused byte arrays using garbage collection.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;JNA (Java Native Access from Sun/Oracle) provides one possible way to solve this problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/twall/jna&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/twall/jna&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Memory is the name of the class that can be used to test the implementation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/twall/jna/blob/master/src/com/sun/jna/Memory.java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/twall/jna/blob/master/src/com/sun/jna/Memory.java&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
